"In April 2004, Minister Wang Xudong, representing the telecoms industry regulator, the Ministry of Information Industry (“MII”), set out to damp down rumours and speculation in the market by indicating that MII was in no hurry to issue the first third generation (“3G”) licences or to impose any particular technology standard and that when and how depended on “the maturity of the technology and market demand.” In other words, China has postponed any definitive decision on when it will issue 3G licences to telecoms carriers."
